notes:
ROOT CAUSE IDENTIFIED:

1. buildDefaultFormDataForExercise (lib/session-form-params.js:123-139) loops over form_parameters_required, calls getLastUsedParameterDisplay for each, and skips any param with no history (if (!lastUsed) continue). With no prior logs, defaults stays empty and the function returns null.

2. handleTimerApplySet (hooks/useTrackerSession.js:101-108) resolves form_data as: setPatch.form_data ?? exerciseWithContext?.default_form_data ?? null. On first use, both are null/undefined → form_data is null.

3. NextSetConfirmModal (line 53) only renders the params section when formData.length > 0. With null form_data → nothing shown, no hint to the user.

4. TimerPanel has NO form parameter input fields at all. The only place to enter them is SessionLoggerModal, which is what Log Set opens directly.

FIX PLAN:
In handleTimerApplySet, after resolving form_data, check if the exercise has form_parameters_required but form_data resolved to null (no history). In that case, redirect to openManualLog (the same path as Edit / Log Set) with the current setPatch as a seed, instead of setting pendingSetPatch. This makes Next Set behave identically to Log Set on first attempt of a param-requiring exercise.

  const resolvedFormData = setPatch.form_data ?? exerciseWithContext?.default_form_data ?? null;
  const hasRequiredParams = (selectedExercise.form_parameters_required ?? []).length > 0;
  if (hasRequiredParams && !resolvedFormData) {
    openManualLog({ side: setPatch.side, seedSet: { ...setPatch, form_data: [] } });
    return;
  }
  setPendingSetPatch({ ...setPatch, form_data: resolvedFormData });

openManualLog is already available in useTrackerSession scope (passed as a prop). No new dependencies needed.
